    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1958-03-16T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1958-03-16T13:00:00-05:00" n="37"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d37">
                <head>37. Telegram From the <gloss type="from">Embassy in Cuba</gloss> to the <gloss
                        type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    <note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d37fn1">Source: Department of State, Central
                        Files, 737.56/3–1658. Secret; Priority.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Havana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1958-03-16T13:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1958—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>543. Guell informed us night March 15: <list>
                        <label>(A)</label>
                        <item>
                            <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> greatly concerned over steps taken
                                <gloss target="#t_DEPTEL1">Deptel</gloss> 492.<note n="2"
                                xml:id="d37fn2">
                                <ref target="#d36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>
                                </ref>.</note>
                        </item>
                        <label>(B)</label>
                        <item>If <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> had been forewarned that <gloss
                                target="#t_MAP1">MAP</gloss> equipment was to be held back, they
                            would have purchased such equipment from other countries.</item>
                        <label>(C)</label>
                        <item>Present <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> equipment is obsolete and
                            worn. As <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> is increasing size of army,
                            it is especially anxious to receive rifles (<gloss target="#t_DEPTEL1"
                                >Deptel</gloss> 492).</item>
                        <label>(D)</label>
                        <item>Guell will as soon as possible prepare note from <gloss
                                target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> to US for presentation.</item>
                        <label>(E)</label>
                        <item>It will be impossible to avoid publicity regarding steps taken <gloss
                                target="#t_DEPTEL1">Deptel</gloss> 492.</item>
                        <label>(F)</label>
                        <item>Reaffirmed that elections will be postponed and when held will be
                            completely honest (<gloss target="#t_EMBTEL1">Embtel</gloss> 536<note
                                n="3" xml:id="d37fn3">
                                <ref target="#d34">Document 34</ref>.</note>).</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>I conveyed assurances that there was no change in friendly attitude of US to
                        <gloss target="#t_GOC1">GOC</gloss> and again pointed out embarrassing
                    position of US due to overwhelming criticism from Congress and press.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SEET1">
                            <hi rend="strong">Smith</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
